  "title": "Gardener",
  "description": "<p>As a Gardener, you will support gardening and landscape operations across designated areas, ensuring that our green spaces are well maintained, healthy, and presentable. Your daily tasks will involve general plant care such as watering, pruning, weeding, fertilizing, and pest control, while using a variety of gardening tools safely and effectively.<br /></p><p><strong>Job Responsibilities</strong></p><p>•\tMonitor and maintain plant health through regular watering and fertilising</p><p>•\tRemove weeds from garden beds and surrounding areas to maintain a clean and tidy appearance</p><p>•\tPerform basic pruning to promote healthy plant growth</p><p>•\tTrim small trees, hedges, shrubs, and grass</p><p>•\tAssist with planting, display setups, loading/unloading, and preparatory work</p><p>•\tClear garden waste such as dead leaves, branches, and other debris</p><p>•\tEnsure safe and proper use, handling, and storage of tools, equipment, fertilisers, and chemicals</p><p>•\tCarry out pest control activities where required</p><p>•\tPerform any other ad-hoc duties assigned by superiors<br /></p><p><strong>Job Requirements</strong></p><p>•\tMinimum 3 years of relevant gardening or landscape maintenance experience</p><p>•\tWSQ certificates related to landscape maintenance are preferred</p><p>•\tExperience in fertiliser and chemical application is an advantage</p><p>•\tFamiliarity with basic hand tools and light handheld machinery</p><p>•\tReliable, detail-oriented, and able to complete tasks in a timely manner</p><p>•\tPassion for outdoor work and nature</p>",
